    "title": "AI & Robotics Snacks — April 25, 2026",
    "date": "2026-04-25",
    "tags": ["DeepSeek V4", "GPT-5.5", "OpenAI Clinicians", "NVIDIA Robotics Week"],
    "fresh": true,
    "content": "**AI & Robotics Snacks** — April 25, 2026\n\n---\n\n## 🐉 DeepSeek Dropped Two Models and Broke the Benchmark Chart (Again)\n\nA year after briefly making every AI lab in America reconsider their life choices, DeepSeek is back — this time with V4-Flash and V4-Pro, both on preview.\n\n- **V4-Pro specs:** 1.6T total parameters, 49B active, 1M token context. SWE-bench Verified: 80.6% — within 0.2 points of Claude Opus 4.6. LiveCodeBench Pass@1: 93.5. Codeforces rating: 3,206, leading GPT-5.4.\n- **V4-Flash specs:** 284B total parameters, 13B active. Priced at $0.14/M input and $0.28/M output — frontier-class coding performance at vending machine prices.\n\n*DeepSeek makes frontier AI look expensive. Frontier AI companies are not pleased.*\n\n**Sources:** [TechCrunch](https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/24/deepseek-previews-new-ai-model-that-closes-the-gap-with-frontier-models/) | [Simon Willison](https://simonwillison.net/2026/Apr/24/deepseek-v4/) | [DeepSeek API Docs](https://api-docs.deepseek.com/news/news260424)\n\n---\n\n## 💸 OpenAI Shipped GPT-5.5. The Model Is Better. The Bill Is Double.\n\nGPT-5.5 — OpenAI's first fully retrained base model since GPT-4.5 — launched April 23–24. Natively omnimodal, it processes all modalities end-to-end, and costs twice as much as its predecessor.\n\n- **Benchmarks:** 82.7% on Terminal-Bench 2.0 (vs. 69.4% for Claude Opus 4.7), 58.6% on SWE-Bench Pro, 78.7% on OSWorld-Verified. On GDPval — knowledge work across 44 real occupations — it matches or beats industry professionals in 84.9% of comparisons.\n- **The price:** API pricing doubled from $2.50/$15 to $5/$30 per million input/output tokens. OpenAI's consolation: it delivers better results with fewer tokens.\n\n*OpenAI doubled the price and called it efficiency. Somewhere an enterprise CFO is staring blankly at a wall.*\n\n**Sources:** [OpenAI](https://openai.com/index/introducing-gpt-5-5/) | [TechCrunch](https://techcrunch.com/2026/04/23/openai-chatgpt-gpt-5-5-ai-model-superapp/) | [VentureBeat](https://venturebeat.com/ai/openais-gpt-5-5-is-here-and-its-no-potato-narrowly-beats-anthropics-claude-mythos-preview-on-terminal-bench-2-0)\n\n---\n\n## 🩺 OpenAI Is Now Also Your Doctor (Technically)\n\nOpenAI launched ChatGPT for Clinicians — a free clinical AI tier for verified U.S. physicians, nurse practitioners, physician assistants, and pharmacists.\n\n- **What it is:** A dedicated ChatGPT interface for licensed US healthcare providers, with license verification. Not consumer health advice — clinician-only access.\n- **The context:** In the span of one week, OpenAI shipped a Pentagon cybersecurity model, a free clinical tool, and GPT-5.5. \"Focus\" remains a loosely-defined concept at OpenAI HQ.\n\n*The company that started as a research nonprofit is now subsidizing your doctor's second opinion.*\n\n**Sources:** [OpenAI News](https://openai.com/news/)\n\n---\n\n## 🤖 NVIDIA Declared National Robotics Week. The Robots Are Learning Accordingly.\n\nFor National Robotics Week, NVIDIA released Isaac GR00T open models enabling robots to understand natural language and execute multi-step tasks via vision-language-action reasoning.\n\n- **The sim-to-real push:** Cadence and NVIDIA partnered to combine Cadence's multiphysics simulation engines with NVIDIA's Isaac libraries and Cosmos world models — specifically targeting the persistent gap between simulated robot training and real-world deployment.\n- **The Mimic benchmark:** Mimic Robotics' video-action model achieved 10x better sample efficiency and 2x faster convergence on real-world manipulation tasks using this stack.\n\n*We're building a national holiday around robots learning to do what humans already do. The robots are, presumably, flattered.*\n\n**Sources:** [NVIDIA Blog](https://blogs.nvidia.com/blog/national-robotics-week-2026/)"
  }
]
